@NODE "Woodland_1" "Woodland_1"

This is the first track I ever created, and as such is rather simple. In fact, it's about as simple as you can get - it's a small rectangular loop. You'd think that this would make the race too easy, but in actual fact the close-quarters nature of the track and the number of trees around the edge make this track substantially more difficult than it would at first appear.

Objects : Watch out for the trees around the edge of the track; the nature of the collision routines in the game mean that these are more difficult to avoid than you'd think. There are also tree-stumps on the track; crashing into these causes you to spin out of control.
@endnode

@node "Woodland_2" "Woodland_2"

This track is set a little deeper in the forest, where a river runs between the trees. The river itself is served by several smaller streams, so be careful with your cornering - you don't want to skid off the track and into the water.

Objects : Trees and tree-stumps again.
@endnode

@node "Woodland_3" "Woodland_3"

This race takes place on a track built high up amongst the treetops. There are a couple of jumps, but you main concern should be your cornering again, as it's all too easy to skid around a corner misjudge your timing and plunge off the side of the track to your doom.

Objects: Tree-stumps.
@endnode

@node "Woodland_4" "Woodland_4"

This track is built even higher up in the treetops. It's also considerably trickier than track 3, containing loads of tight ninety-degree corners and tons of tricky jumps.

Objects: Tree-stumps.
@endnode
